{{Coord missing|Tanzania}} [[Image:Map of Zanzibar Archipelago-en.svg|thumb|The Zanzibar Archipelago]] The '''Zanzibar Archipelago''' consists of several islands lying off the coast of [[East Africa]] in the [[Indian Ocean]]. There are four main islands, three primary islands with human populations, a fourth coral island that serves as an essential breeding ground for seabirds, plus a number of smaller islets that surround them and an isolated tiny islet.<ref>{{cite book|title=Africa Overland |author=Lizzie Williams|year= 2005|publisher=New Holland Publishers|isbn=1-77007-187-3}}</ref>
Most of the archipelago belongs to the [[Zanzibar]] semi-autonomous region of [[Tanzania]], while [[Mafia Island]] and its associated islets fall under the suzerainty of the [[Pwani Region]] on the mainland.
==List of islands in the Zanzibar Archipelago==
