{{Infobox Islands | name = Alphonse Group | image name = Alphonse Group.png | image caption = Satellite Image of Alphonse Group | image size = | locator map = Se-map.gif | native name = | native name link = | nickname = | location = [[Indian Ocean]] | coordinates = {{coord|7|05|S|52|44|E|display=inline,title|region:SC_type:isle_source:dewiki}} | archipelago = Seychelles | total islands = 3 | major islands = Alphonse Island | area_km2 = 2.211 | highest mount = | elevation_m = | country = Seychelles | country admin divisions title = | country admin divisions = | country admin divisions title 1 = | country admin divisions 1 = | country admin divisions title 2 = | country admin divisions 2 = | country capital city = | country largest city = | country largest city population = | country leader title = | country leader name = | population = 82 | population as of = | density_km2 = 37 | ethnic groups = | additional info = }} {{Location map |Indian Ocean |label=Alphonse Group |lon_dir=E |lat_dir=S |lat_deg=7|lat_min=05 |lon_deg=52|lon_min=44 |position=right |width=250 |float=right |mark=Cercle rouge 100%.svg |marksize=20 |caption=Location of the Alphonse Group in the Indian Ocean }}
The '''Alphonse Group''' belong to the [[Outer Islands (Seychelles)|Outer Islands]] of the [[Seychelles]], lying in the southwest of the island nation, {{convert|403|km|mi|abbr=off}} southwest the capital, [[Victoria, Seychelles|Victoria]], on [[Mahé, Seychelles|Mahé]] Island. The closest island is [[Desnœufs Island]] of the [[Amirante Islands]], {{convert|87|km|0|abbr=on}} further north.
==Islands in the Alphonse Group== The Alphonse Group consists of two atolls that are only {{convert|2|km|mi|spell=in|abbr=off}} apart, separated by a deep channel: #[[Alphonse Atoll]] in the north, with only one island, Alphonse Island #[[St. François Atoll]] in the south, with the islands St. François and Bijoutier
Only Alphonse Island is inhabited. The aggregate land area of all three islets in both atolls is than {{convert|2.21|km2|0|abbr=on}}, but the total area including reefs and lagoons amounts to roughly {{convert|65|km2|0|abbr=on}}.<ref>[http://www.seychelles.travel/en/about_seychelles/island.php?rc=1&aid=57 The Islands of the Seychelles]</ref>
